ne.\r\n        <li>Aspects, many-one identity and stages -- different routes to the same destination?, 53th eidos meeting (\"Themes from Baxter\"), 28th of May.\r\n        <li>Exemplification, Parthood and Constitution, 53th eidos meeting (\"Themes from Baxter\"), 27th of May.\r\n        <li>Aspects and Respects, 53th eidos meeting (\"Themes from Baxter\"), 26th of May.\r\n        <li>Representation: relational, but intrinsic, SOPHA Paris, 6th of May.\r\n        <li>Why there are no relations, eidos research colloquium, 2nd of May.\r\n        <li>Racisme et b&ecirc;tise, interview with the French radio station \"Radio France Internationale\", Caroline Lachowsky, Autour de la question, 2nd  of May.\r\n        <li>Lessons from Russell, 52th eidos meeting (\"Moore, Russell, etc.\"), 28th of April.\r\n        <li>L'&eacute;nigme de la repr&eacute;sentation, research seminar Neuch&acirc;tel, 28th of February.\r\n        <li>Grounding Modality in Essence, \"Logic and Metaphysics of Essence\", Istituto di Filosofia Applicata ISFA, Lugano, 13th of January.\r\n      </ul>\r\n    <li>2011\r\n      <ul>\r\n        <li>Theories of time, presentism, persistence and the real problem of change, Geneva, 14th of December.\r\n        <li>Humean Supervenience - Not Quite Dead Yet, Hume's Metaphysics and Humean Metaphysics, Tampere, Finland, 4th of June.\r\n        <li>Exemplification as Parthood, Geneva, 11th of June.\r\n        <li>What Universals Essentially Are, Geneva, 10th of June.\r\n        <li>Heterogeneous Simples, Geneva, 29th of May.\r\n        <li>Representation and intentionality: where intrinsicness/extrinsicness and non-/relationality crosscut, Geneva, 28th of May.\r\n        <li>comments on Goncalo Santos, Unlimited Possibilities, GVA-BCN meeting, Barcelona, 12th of May.\r\n        <li>In Favour of Determinable Universals, Geneva, 23rd of April.\r\n        <li>Why There Are No Tropes, Geneva, 22nd of April.\r\n        <li>Rigid Referene is Existential Dependence, eidos